	<h1 class="title-header">Update on School Closure</h1>
	<div class="entry-meta">
		<span class="by-author">By <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://armstrong.k12.il.us/author/dloschen/" title="View all posts by Darren" rel="author">Darren</a></span> </span>in <span class="category"><a href="https://armstrong.k12.il.us/category/school-news/" rel="category tag">News</a>, <a href="https://armstrong.k12.il.us/category/school-news/school-news-school-news/" rel="category tag">School News</a></span> on <span class="datetime"><a href="https://armstrong.k12.il.us/school-news/update-on-school-closure/" title="10:51 am" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2020-04-17T10:51:36-05:00" pubdate>April 17, 2020</time></a></span>.	</div>
<!-- end .entry-meta -->

	<div class="entry-content clearfix">
		<p>This is not the news I wanted to share but our school will be closed for in person instruction for the rest of 2019-2020 school year.  Remote learning will remain in place for the remainder of the school year and paper packets will still also be available for students without internet access. Lunches will continue to be made for Monday pickups. More information about activities that were planned in May will be coming  soon.  Students continue to get your work done as best you can.  Remember if there was work you did not finish from the 3rd quarter–get that turned in as well. Everyone please stay safe.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">College express students and dual enrollment students–elearning will begin on March 30 through DACC for you.  Please stay safe.</span></p>
	</div>
<!-- end .entry-content -->

